        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The current military posture and activity patterns suggest a high level of operational tempo, with multiple aircraft and vessels engaged in various missions worldwide. The presence of T-38 aircraft in training exercises and the deployment of the USS Tripoli with the 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit indicate a focus on readiness and preparedness. The tracking of H-60 helicopters and other aircraft on patrol missions suggests a continued emphasis on maritime security and surveillance. The overall assessment is that the US military is maintaining a strong and active presence globally, with a focus on training, readiness, and operational support.</description>
